@@ySunward Causeway of Thirst@@N~
@@yA hard sun beats down on scalloped dunes, turning every ridge into flowing brass and fire.@@N
@@lBlue-painted waystones rise from the ground at measured intervals, their edges smoothed by years of grit.@@N
@@yYellow pennants tied to bone-dry stakes flutter in restless bursts, then fall silent all at once.@@N
@@bBrown dust clings to every surface, muting color and scent until only thirst seems real.@@N
@@yThe hunt for a true oasis continues, each step pressing deeper into an intentional desert route.@@N
