@@yDry thorn and brittle reed roots poke from the sand, stubborn signs that water once lingered nearby.@@N
@@lShallow shadows pool beneath slate-colored stones, giving brief relief from the blazing glare.@@N
@@yYellow chalk lines on nearby stone point onward, renewed by many hands over many seasons.@@N
@@bDark brown pebbles ring the trail like spilled beads, worn smooth by wind and travel.@@N
@@yEven in the heat, a faint cool promise hangs in the air and urges you onward.@@N
